-- Russia’s Defense Minister Serdyukov May Resign, RBC Daily Says
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2012-04-05T04:27:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-05/russia-s-defense-minister-serdyukov-may-resign-rbc-daily-says.html
Russian Defense Minister Anatoly Serdyukov may quit when the country forms a new government after
 Vladimir Putin ’s presidential inauguration next month,  RBC Daily 
reported, citing unidentified people.  Serdyukov and Nikolai Makarov, the head of the Russian
military’s General Staff, asked not to be re-appointed by the
new government, which will be headed by outgoing president
 Dmitry Medvedev , newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
 ikhrennikov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Viljoen at 
 jviljoen@bloomberg.net  